description:
Define and document the complete wire format for all content written to khorshid-social Issues.

Encrypted payload wrapper (for comments and posts):
  { v: 1, n: '<12-byte nonce b64>', c: '<AES-256-GCM ciphertext b64>' }

Decrypted payload types:
  Post (rooms only):
    { type: 'post', body: '...', sent_at: <unix ms> }

  Comment (channels and rooms):
    { type: 'comment', post_id: '<channel/postnum>', reply_to: '<target comment sha>', body: '...', sent_at: <unix ms> }

  Vote (plaintext, NOT encrypted):
    { type: 'vote', target_id: '<sha256 of target comment body>', signal: 'up' | 'important', vote_id: '<sha256(privkey || target_id) b64>', sent_at: <unix ms> }

  Flag (plaintext, NOT encrypted):
    { type: 'flag', target_id: '<sha256 of target comment body>', vote_id: '<sha256(privkey || target_id) b64>', sent_at: <unix ms> }

Notes:
- vote_id is a commitment hash: same user, same target = same hash. Enables dedup without revealing sender pubkey.
- Votes and flags are plaintext so the GH Actions aggregator can read them without decryption.
- All encrypted content uses AES-256-GCM. Public rooms: hardcoded per-room key. Private rooms: key from invite bundle.
